{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3485074,"name":"","username":"SirFire","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/sirfire/{size}/222590_2.png","created_at":"2025-01-16T22:40:39.278Z","cooked":"<p>We are using direct angle control for our driving, which is working as expected both in simulation and in real-life. We also have PathPlanner’s on-the-fly path generation integrated into a <code>Command</code>, which also works as expected. (Not very accurate sometimes and seems to have a deadband where it just won’t try to be more accurate beyond that, but that’s besides the point.)</p>
<p>The issue is that when I run the on-the-fly path gen, it rotates to the target rotation but when the command ends, the robot snaps right back to whatever the previously commanded heading was by the human driver. We need it to stay at whatever heading the command ended with. We have this same problem with PathPlanner autos. Note that so far I’ve only been able to try this in simulation, not real-life, so I’m not sure if the behavior is the same in both but my guess is that it is.</p>
<p>Side note on this, anyone know how to increase accuracy for autos (namely on-the-fly generation) and make it more sensitive? The robot will go to roughly the right place but if it overshoots, it doesn’t try to go back and correct itself or anything.</p>
<p><strong>Edit:</strong> Link to our code: <a href="http://github.com/RoNexRobotics/Swerve8551" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">GitHub - RoNexRobotics/Swerve8551</a></p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2025-01-16T22:53:23.201Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":14,"reads":147,"readers_count":146,"score":119.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":482165,"topic_slug":"direct-heading-control-issues","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://github.com/RoNexRobotics/Swerve8551","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - RoNexRobotics/Swerve8551","clicks":4}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54317,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Main Programmer Dude | 8551"},"post_url":"/t/direct-heading-control-issues/482165/1","custom_user_title":"Main Programmer Dude | 8551","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true,"can_vote":false},{"id":3485132,"name":"Emre Candabakoğlu","username":"emrecandabak","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/e/838e76/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-01-16T23:26:16.776Z","cooked":"<p>Looking at the advanced swerve drive command example from <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span>, I’ve noticed this part:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">
    // Prevent Movement After Auto
    if (resetHeading)
    {
      if (headingX == 0 &amp;&amp; headingY == 0 &amp;&amp; Math.abs(headingAdjust.getAsDouble()) == 0)
      {
        // Get the curret Heading
        Rotation2d currentHeading = swerve.getHeading();

        // Set the Current Heading to the desired Heading
        headingX = currentHeading.getSin();
        headingY = currentHeading.getCos();
      }
      //Dont reset Heading Again
      resetHeading = false;
    }

</code></pre>
<p>Probably something you should consider doing as well. I’m not very familiar with <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span>, but I recommend you do it by using “beforeStarting” to have this functionality in the drive command factory. This way it will not move after auto when the command runs for the first time, and it will reset the heading target after joystickdrive command gets interrupted by the aprilTagAlign command.</p>
